ity in their society that led to recognition of sanctity. "A tremendous piece of scholarship. . . . This journey through more than 2,000 saints is anything but dull. Along the way, Schulenburg informs our ideas regarding the role of saints in the medieval psyche, gender-specific identification, and the heroics of virginity." -Library Journal "[This book] will be a kind of 'roots' experience for some readers. They will hear the voices, haunted and haunting, of their distant ancestors and understand more about themselves." -Christian Science Monitor "This fascinating book reaches far beyond the history of Christianity to recreate the 'herstory' of a whole gender." -Kate Saunders, The Independent  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUChP eBook-Package Archive 1990-1999z978311066785140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226518992423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226518992.jpg  a978-3-11-066785-1  UChP eBook-Package Archive 1990-1999c1990d1999  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles